spanGrp.span: Me, I will tell a story
Me, in the old days when I married
I arrived and they were saying there is a way to prepare animal skins
qayit aa iyahit ge gesinaj dung'wendajeg
nilifika na wakawa wanasema huwa kuna utengenezaji wa ngozi
Often they would prepare goat skins, often your husband would give you money and you would go to buy a skin, and you come and prepare and and later you put it in the traditional mixture of chemicals
gegudaj aqod mboyd geajeny mboyd am yit gagony gwargw lapi aa gusha agwaygagw aamid gugudii am ihidi gwandij guhor gubut jed
gegudaj aqod mboyd geajeny mboyd am yit gagony gwargw lapi aa gusha agwaygagw aamid gugudii am ihidi gwandij guhor gubut jed
huwa wanatengenezaga kwa ngozi ya mbuzi huwa mume wako anakupa pesa na unaenda kununua ngozi hiyo naukija unaitengeneza baadaye unaweka kwenye muozo au kemikali ya asili
You will spread the oil before putting in the mixture
aa ab hij aa gihescha aha ar ja yin jed guhor
aa ab hij aa gihescha aha ar ja yin jed guhor
hapo utakuwa umeipaka mafuta kabla ya kuiweka kwenye hiyo kemikali
You leave it for three days in the mixture, then after that you take it out and dry it
giyin jeed guhor a gwalil awojig samog aa gilal aa gingor
giyin jeed guhor a gwalil awojig samog aa gilal aa gingor
unaiacha siku tatu kwenye kemikali baada ya hapo unaitoa na kuianika
You dry it and after that you sew it with those special threads
gingor am wa gwahit ginuny aa gibashad aa ginuny nabischen amwa gwahit gwand gesinaj dayeg
gingor am wa gwahit ginuny aa gibashad aa ginuny nabischen amwa gwahit gwand gesinaj dayeg
unaanika na baada ya hapo unachana na kuishona unaviweka zile kambakamba maalum
You come and prepare it and there is a thing called nyabuld
unakuja kuitengeneza na kuna kitu kinaitwa nyabuld
The seams you make by inserting those small threads, later you close it, and after that it will be ready and you wear your skin
nyabuld gibashad aa hanang'w ginuny achibad dayes am ng'at ginuny dug qut am wa qwahit gununy akeal dung'wendang'w gohida
'nyabuld gibashad aa hanang''w ginuny achibad dayes am ng''at ginuny dug qut am wa qwahit gununy akeal dung''wendang''w gohida'
kiungo unaichana na unakuja kuyiingiza zile kamba ndogo baadaye unaifunga mdomo wake baada ya hapo itakuea tayari unaivaa ngozi yako
It has the sapsapt threads put on it
That is, there are a lot of them
Threads, threads, threads, often you put them until it is full and you wear your skin but often they wear those of a goat, they don't wear those of sheep
sabadang sabadang sabadang giyin aa geanyit sabadangagu gikwal aqod dang'w gekwalaj agwag nog gichay ga gisilg mekwala
'sabadang sabadang sabadang giyin aa geanyit sabadangagu gikwal aqod dang''w gekwalaj agwag nog gichay ga gisilg mekwala'
makamba kamba huwa unaweka mpaka zijae na unavaa ngozi yako lakini huwa wavaa za mbizi za kondoo haivaliwi
This is how it was, even in the old my mother
ndiyo ilikuwa hivyo hata zamani mama yangu
Even she was doing this work
hata yeye alikuwa anafanyaga kazi hiyo
She was preparing skins and later she was applying oil and putting in the mixture and left it in pieces and then came to sew it
is gagut amwa gwahit qwahesh iwaqwahit gwayin qujehed am ng'at qon qabashad am wa qwahit qon qwanap
'is gagut amwa gwahit qwahesh iwaqwahit gwayin qujehed am ng''at qon qabashad am wa qwahit qon qwanap'
anaandaa ngozi na baada ya hapo anapaka na kuweka kwenye kemikali na baadaye anachacha katika vipande vipande na kuja kuishona
She then told the children "Don't you see this work that you all will go to do when you go to be married?" and it's true, now I understand
aa gway moda debuga much ar iyoway galgagw gadiyed ja away asin aa nihi aka huma ar anin gadagsej gew
aa gway moda debuga much ar iyoway galgagw gadiyed ja away asin aa nihi aka huma ar anin gadagsej gew
akawambia watoto hamuoni kazi mtakayoenda kufanya siku mkienda zenu kuolewa na ni kweli mimi sasa nimejionea
Even me, when I arrived I did the work that was done by my mother
iyahid ar anin gasiny gadiyan qay sinaj qamatenyun
iyahid ar anin gasiny gadiyan qay sinaj qamatenyun
hata mimi nilipofika nikafanya kazi iliyofanywa na mama yangu
I will come to tear the small pieces and sew them and later wear my skin and it the skin for your back is done
gidon dabashad gidon danapi am ng'at gakwal aqodeny agesin ar aqod badayd nd gwand ar aqod badayd
'gidon dabashad gidon danapi am ng''at gakwal aqodeny agesin ar aqod badayd nd gwand ar aqod badayd'
nitakuja nipasue vipande vipande na kuishona na badae naivaa ngozi yangu na inafanywa ngozi ya mgongo
For the skin for your back they often sew beads
And you come to wear it together with your skin, especially if there is a dance or circumcision ceremony or a ceremonial dance called qadoweed
aa ginuny akwaludayewi dung'wendang' qwarany awechand sib gey ba gwand dumd qan ge gwand luqumajeng qany ge gwand qadowed yani
'aa ginuny akwaludayewi dung''wendang'' qwarany awechand sib gey ba gwand dumd qan ge gwand luqumajeng qany ge gwand qadowed yani'
na unakuja kuivaa pamoja na ngozi yako hasa siku kama kuna ngoma au sherehe za jando kwa vijana au ngoma za ibada(qadowed)
You wear your skin on your back and a small skin like a skirt
gikwak aqod badayd aa dung'endang'w ha ba
'gikwak aqod badayd aa dung''endang''w ha ba'
unavaa ngozi ya mgongo na ngozi ndogo kama asketi
And often we are very beautiful, it's not a joke, we put metal on our arms and our necks and other things
is aa geawasch miyas diya nung'wad budayd ar jeed uu geanawj shetkajegas gesiny daroyekas geanawj alanjed
'is aa geawasch miyas diya nung''wad budayd ar jeed uu geanawj shetkajegas gesiny daroyekas geanawj alanjed'
na huwa tunakuwaga wazuri sana hebu acha utani tunasuka vyuma vya mikononi na shingoni na tunasuka vitu vingine vingi
That is, if you pass by you resemble the clouds
sen is guwujew shunog ar ing'ati
yaani hata ukipita unafanana na mawingu
